[48;2;43;48;59m[39m  270, 270[0m:[39m[48;2;43;48;59m [38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;235;203;139mStep 4: Validate medical accuracy with entity comparison.[38;2;235;203;139m**[38;2;192;197;206m This is the safety-critical step. You extract medical entities (medications, conditions, dosages, procedures) from both the original clinical text and the simplified version, then compare them. If the original mentions "clopidogrel 75mg daily" and the simplified version says "a blood thinner" without specifying the name or dose, that's a meaning loss that needs to be caught. Comprehend Medical handles the entity extraction. The comparison logic checks that every medication, dosage, and condition from the source appears in the output. Skip this step and you're trusting the LLM to never drop or alter a medical fact. It will. Not often, but often enough to matter.[K
